15... Rg8
{ We will not be merciful here. We are going to recapture our lost pawn immediately. }
16. Qh6 Rxg2 17. Ne2
{ Although this move appears pointless, surprisingly, it's the engine choice, White opens the way for the b2-Bishop and attacks our f6-Knight. }
17... Rg6
{ I'll add the remaining analysis as clickables because I think it's almost impossible to reach such a position on the board.   18.Qh3  Qc7  19.f4  O-O-O  20.f5  exf5  21.Rf1  Kb8  22.O-O-O  Ne8  23.Rxf5  Nd6  24.Rxc5  Nxc4  25.Rxc4  Qxa5  26.Ra4  Qg5  This sample continuation shows how much the position is alive and playable for both sides. }
