{ Kicking our f2-bishop and indirectly increasing the pressure on the f7-pawn. }
11... Bc5 12. Ng5 { Unleashing the full pressure on the f7-pawn. } 12... Nxe5
{ A beautiful move, and it would be much more awesome if capturing was forced in chess or at least when we wish it to be ;@@EndBracket@@ }
13. Qxe5
{ Because why not!? The move  13...Re8  is impossible, and f7-pawn is under attack; it seems illogical to ignore the material gain! }
13... d5
{ Resembling the d6-push we have seen multiple times. Now the f7-pawn is defended, the way for our c8-bishop is open, and White's c4-Bishop is under attack. White is not lost from an evaluation perspective, but psychologically he is on the back foot. It's tough to think that you are winning easily, and then suddenly you have to find multiple only moves just to survive. }
14. Bxd5
{ I believe this is the easier capture although both captures are equal in the engine's eyes. }
14... Bg4+ { Developing and attacking White's miserable King. } 15. Kd2 Rfe8
{ Preparing the killer Be3 check. White must sacrifice the Queen and take the perpetual or walk away empty-handed. }
16. Bxf7+
{ The only move was  16.Nxf7!  Rxe5  17.Nh6  Kh8  18.Nf7  and take the draw by repetition. Now White got greedy and is lost. }
16... Kh8 17. Bxe8 { The coming Be3 check forces White to grab the Rook. }
17... Rd8+ 18. Kc3 Qb4# { GG } *

