{ The only way to play for an advantage and perhaps complicate things. } 4...
Nxd5 5. d4
{ The engine likes this move at first but changes its mind after a few moves. }
5... Nxc3 { We wreck White's pawn structure and intend to target it next. } 6.
bxc3 g6
{ We will fianchetto our f8-Bishop since the a1-h8 diagonal looks promising for us. }
7. Bb5+ Bd7 { The simplest. } 8. Bxd7+ Qxd7 9. Ne5
{ A one-move threat without a clear follow-up. } 9... Qd5
{ We run and attack. } 10. O-O Bg7
{ We continue our development. We will follow it up with castling, and according to White's choices, we can either go ...Nc6 or ...Rc8 immediately. }
*

