{ After White has managed to play like an engine for the better part of the game an endgame is reached, where despite the fact that material is even, White's position is slightly more favorable due to the weak, isolated e-pawn. I believe the endgame is holdable with correct defense, but it's hard to expect more than a draw. I am ready to take risks from a personal perspective, especially in faster time controls. But of course, if you prefer a different style of positions, I advise checking the alternative 8...d6. The play may continue as such:   16.Rxf8  Kxf8  17.Bf4  Bd7  18.Rf1  Ke7  19.Bg5  Ke8  20.Bd3  Be7  +=  ED: Model Game with the Endgame }
