{ You might be thinking you're missing something, but you are not! Simply White is giving up his e4-pawn while thinking he/she might have some crazy sacrifices on the f7-square. So let's focus on this only idea. }
3... Nxe4 4. Bxf7+ { White is committed to his sacrifices. } 4... Kxf7 5. Ne5+
Kg8 { Not the only winning move, but it's more than enough. } 6. Qf3
{ Threatening both our Knight and the mate on the f7-square. } 6... Nf6
{ We simply refuted White's threats, and White is left with a totally losing position. }
